Part 2

Comparing the genes which are different in patients and controls and what happens upon PANO treatment

## Not surprising, there are plenty of DEgenes upon PANO treatment. However, the intersting sets are the 403 DEgenes which even after PANO treatment still are different. These most likely represent a set of genes that are inheritantly different between individual human beings, based on geographic location, age, environment etc. The other 116 genes that are only different in patients in DMSO treatmeent but not anymore upon PANO treatment could be the one that need to be rescued to make the patients more like controls

## 116 genes are not differentially expressed anymore upon PANO treatment. 45 were going down and 71 were going up.
## 403 genes are differentially expressed upon DMSO or PANO treatment. 131 go down in both and 236 go up in both. 20 are down in DMSO but up in PANO and 16 are up in DMSO and then down in PANO.
## about those DEgenes that aren't anymore upon PANO treatment. Do they fall into a specific cluster we defined previously for the DEgenes in DMSO ctrl vs patients?

## how do the notDEanymore genes look like on a heatmap?
